category: RIVERS OF AFRICA
category comment: 

clue: The Nile has 3 main sections: the Atbara & the ones known by these 2 colors

response: Blue & White

clue: The Congo River was renamed this from 1971 to 1997; the Democratic Republic also had that name

response: Zaire

clue: The mighty Okavango River  stretches from Angola to this desert in Botswana, where it becomes a swamp

response: the Kalahari Desert

clue: The Draa River in Morocco is also called this 4-letter Arabic word for an intermittent stream

response: Wadi

clue: Rivers called the Black, Red & White this flow through Burkina Faso, which used to be called Upper this

response: Volta

